# Haskell Profiling and Performance

## General

You must compile the program and all dependencies with the profiling option

## Performance Profiling

Run the program with the options

    +RTS -s -p -RTS

* **-s** creates a summary on standart output, with short information on memory, garbage collection and execution time usage.
* **-p** create a file _programName.prof_ file with cost center based information. Use normal editor to read.

## Memory Profiling

Run the program with the options
    
    +RTS -s -hd -RTS

